oncepts such as tastes, ideas, skills, politics, and economic forces. Through investigating a range of contrasting cropscapes spanning millennia and the globe, the authors break open traditional historical structures of period, geography, and direction to glean insight into previously invisible actors and forces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCropsxHistory. 0aHistoriographyxMethodology. 0aWorld historyxHistoriography. 70(DE-588)4020832-10(DE-627)10631663X0(DE-576)208934979aGewalt2gnd 70(DE-588)4027089-00(DE-627)1062861020(DE-576)208969136aInnovation2gnd 70(DE-588)4038639-90(DE-627)1062312860(DE-576)209031298aMensch2gnd 70(DE-588)4051157-10(DE-627)1061783690(DE-576)209091630aSachkultur2gnd 70(DE-588)4055736-40(DE-627)1042704700(DE-576)209115173aSoziale Ungleichheit2gnd 70(DE-588)4120658-70(DE-627)1043768640(DE-576)209536934aLebensraum2gnd 70(DE-588)7751254-60(DE-627)6638551790(DE-576)33844176XaVerhaltensökonomie2gnd 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh1 aHahn, Barbara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLourdusamy, John Bosco, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSaraiva, Tiago, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030026842340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97